The FCGBDS is a layered, multi-signal, horizontally scalable bot detection and
policy enforcement system written in TypeScript on top of Express.js, Redis,
and PostgreSQL. It runs as production middleware in the API backend and makes
a real-time allow/challenge/block decision before a single byte of application
logic executes.

It is not a WAF. It is not a CAPTCHA wall. It is not rate limiting with a fancy
name. It is a confidence scoring engine that analyzes the request itself and
makes a forward decision based on a normalized 0–100 risk score derived from
multiple independent signal families.


