THE DECISION ENGINE: createOwnerBotDefenseMiddleware()
(Source: api/src/index.ts — independently verified)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Every protected request passes through this function. The decision tree:

  STEP 1 — WAF Bypass Exemption
  ───────────────────────────────
  Internal monitoring, health checks, and synthetic tests carry a verified
  x-fcg-test-token header. Matching token = instant allow at score 0,
  profile 'whitelist'. Nothing else runs. This keeps test traffic out of
  the bot signal corpus.

  STEP 2 — Profile Resolution (getOwnerDefenseThresholds)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Three threshold profiles, selected by incoming path:

  ┌──────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬───────────────┬──────────────┐
  │ Profile      │ Max IP/min   │ Max Dev/min  │ Max Payload   │ Max Token    │
  │              │              │              │ Repeat/2min   │ Anomalies    │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┼───────────────┼──────────────┤
  │ auth-write   │ 50           │ 40           │ 20            │ 4            │
  │ mscb-write   │ 20           │ 15           │ 8             │ 3            │
  │ default      │ 25           │ 20           │ 10            │ 3            │
  └──────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────┴───────────────┴──────────────┘

  MSCB paths (OAuth start/callback, session health, bridge-control) run the
  tightest profile because they are the highest-value attack target.

  STEP 3 — Signal Scoring (additive, capped at 100)
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  See signal families below.

  STEP 4 — Decision
  ──────────────────
  normalizedScore = min(100, max(0, rawScore))
  confidence      = normalizedScore / 100  (0.0 – 1.0 float)

  score ≥ 90   →  HTTP 403  action: 'block'      code: 'request_blocked'
  score ≥ 60   →  HTTP 429  action: 'challenge'  code: 'challenge_required'
  score < 60   →  HTTP 200  action: 'allow'       → next()

  Every outcome logged via [BotDefense][OwnerDecision] with action,
  confidence, score, ruleIds, profile, method, path, uaFingerprint.
  No raw IPs stored. No user identifiers stored.


