THE REDIS STATE LAYER (api/src/services/botDefenseRedis.ts)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Redis key schema:
  bot-defense:ip:<key>              → IP hit counter (INCR + EXPIRE)
  bot-defense:device:<key>          → device fingerprint hit counter
  bot-defense:payload:<key>         → payload signature hit counter
  bot-defense:token-anomaly:<key>   → token anomaly hit counter

Operations:
  recordHit(type, key, windowMs) → Redis INCR + EXPIRE; returns new count
  getHitCount(type, key)         → Redis GET; returns current count
  clearKey(type, key)            → Redis DEL; clears confirmed false-positives
  getStats()                     → SCAN per-prefix for monitoring dashboard

Failure model:
  Primary: Redis INCR + EXPIRE (distributed, auto-expiring, shared)
  Fallback: bounded in-process Map (max 2,000 entries, 120 hits per key)
  On Redis failure: logs warning, uses in-process — enforcement NEVER goes dark.
  Graceful degradation, not silent failure.

Horizontal scaling:
  Multiple API pods share the same Redis cluster. No coordination overhead.
  Works on one server. Works on 20. No code change required.


