share signal intelligence with everyone on the bridge.

AUTHENTICATION
───────────────
Every request signed with HMAC-SHA256:

  Headers required:
    x-fcgbds-ts:        Unix timestamp in milliseconds
    x-fcgbds-signature: hex(hmac_sha256(shared_secret, "${ts}.${jsonBody}"))

  Enforcement:
    • Timestamp skew: max 5 minutes (configurable via FCGBDS_BRIDGE_MAX_SKEW_MS)
    • Comparison: crypto.timingSafeEqual() — timing-attack-safe
    • Missing or invalid signature: HTTP 401, no further processing

THE FOUR ENDPOINTS
───────────────────

  POST /api/fcgbds/bridge/signal/ingest
    Purpose: External platforms report risk signals they have observed.
    Accepts:  platform, signalType, confidence (0–1), channelId, streamId,
              sourceClass, evidence (object), observedAt
    Routing:  confidence ≥ 0.85 → high-priority queue
    Persists: operationsAuditLog (eventType: bridge_signal_ingest)
    Buffer:   Last 500 signals held in memory for /stats endpoint

  POST /api/fcgbds/bridge/session/attest
    Purpose:  Classify a session as verified or unverified human attention.
    Verified when: confidence ≥ 0.7 AND sourceClass ≠ 'unknown_embed'
    Persists: operationsAuditLog (eventType: bridge_session_attest)
    Returns:  { verified, confidence, sourceClass, reason, policyVersion }
    This feeds directly into Proof-of-Rot reward weight — only attested
    sessions earn full engagement credit.

  POST /api/fcgbds/bridge/policy/evaluate
    Purpose:  Real-time policy decision for any session context.
    Risk score computation:
      Base:               0.50
      onsite_first_party: −0.25
      approved_embed:     −0.10
      unknown_embed:      +0.25
      low confidence:     +(1 − confidence) × 0.40
      Final:              clamped 0.0 – 1.0

    Decision mapping:
      riskScore ≥ 0.75 → quarantine  (rewardWeight: 0)
      riskScore ≥ 0.50 → deweight    (rewardWeight: 0.2)
      riskScore < 0.50 → allow       (rewardWeight: 1)

    On quarantine or deweight: fires outbound webhooks immediately to all
    configured partner endpoints — no polling required. Webhooks are also
    HMAC-SHA256 signed so partners can verify authenticity.
    Persists: operationsAuditLog (bridge_policy_evaluate + bridge_webhook_dispatch)

  POST /api/fcgbds/bridge/enforcement/callback
    Purpose:  Platforms report what they actually did with a recommendation.
    This closes the loop. The system knows not just what it recommended but
    what the downstream platform enforced. Feeds back into the signal corpus.
    Persists: operationsAuditLog (bridge_enforcement_callback)

PERSISTENCE AND AUDIT
──────────────────────
  Every bridge event is written to operationsAuditLog via Prisma:
  {
    id:           crypto.randomUUID()
    assignmentId: platform:streamId (or fallback)
    eventType:    bridge_signal_ingest | bridge_session_attest |
                  bridge_policy_evaluate | bridge_enforcement_callback |
                  bridge_webhook_dispatch
    actor:        'fcgbds_bridge'
    details:      JSON string of full event payload
  }

  Fail-open design: if the DB write fails, the bridge endpoint still responds
  so platform integrations are not blocked by database degradation.


